Merge pull request #104 from elukey/master

Reduce DNS lookups for the statsd domain

Reduce DNS lookups for the statsd domain

The sendto socket call is very flexible but it currently
issue a DNS lookup for the statsd domain for every
metric in the for loop to push. This change ensures that
only one lookup is performed for each batch of metrics
to send. It is particularly useful when logster runs
every minute and the number of metrics to push is very high.

Merge pull request #46 from rafael81/logster-master

Add Amazon CloudWatch
Make sure that graphite socket is closed, even if there is an exception while it is open.

Write all data to graphite socket.

The socket.send() method does not guarantee that all data will be
sent. Either use socket.sendall() instead, or check the return value
from send() and loop to send all the data. This is a nasty cause of
intermittent, hard-to-find bugs.

Merge pull request #14 from msabramo/add-logtail-option

Add a --logtail option so that the user can specify a location for logtail other than /usr/sbin/logtail2

Improved accuracy and reliability of percentile calculations

Fixed some problems with percentiles for non-integer values. Improved
this and also coped better with arbitrary percentile values (especially
100% i.e. max).

Generalised MetricLogster extracts time unit from log line

When pushing into Ganglia, the unit for the time metrics will now be
extracted from the log lines - it is assumed that metrics with the same
name will share the same unit; the parser will simply use the first it
encounters in the event they do not.

Allowed operator to configure different time units. Unit does not need
to appear in the log statement as this would be an unnecessary
restriction.

Improved the MetricLogster with capability to calculate distribution
statistics of time metrics.

Add a --logtail option so that the user can specify a location for logtail
other than /usr/sbin/logtail2
